how do you know if someone is bipolar in general they will experience dramatic mood swings that affect their lives and those around them the mood swings are not simple everyday mood changes but swings that tend to last for awhile for example a person might be manic for weeks and experience depression for months there may be periods of normal moods in between manic symptoms include spending sprees talking fast thinking fast and out loud not needing sleep increased sexual activity driving fast depressed signs crying suicidal not eating losing weight gaining weight sleeping all the time negative thoughts these are some of the symptoms but others can occur please don't confuse moodiness with bipolar there is a major difference Bipolar disorder Clinical depression Psychosis Mania Schizophrenia Antipsychotic Antidepressant Maprotiline Hypoglycemia DSM-IV Codes Traumatic brain injury Anger management Electroconvulsive therapy Schizoaffective disorder Mental illness Super Size Me Mixed state (psychology) Clomipramine Adult attention-deficit disorder Dieting Anorexia nervosa Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Haloperidol Doxepin Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Sleep Cognitive therapy Mood stabilizer Cyclothymia Lamotrigine English grammar Paroxetine Atkins Nutritional Approach Narcolepsy Stroke Inflation Urinary incontinence Diabetes mellitus Sexual addiction Diazepam Postpartum depression Prostate cancer Stuttering Bupropion Venlafaxine Child sexuality Emil Kraepelin Anxiety Murder Psychopharmacology Alcoholism Coeliac disease Suicide methods Epilepsy Parkinson's disease Menstrual cycle Common cold Insomnia Sleep apnea Bulgarian language Polycystic ovary syndrome The Catcher in the Rye Dysmenorrhea Grief Grammatical aspect Hypnosis Post-traumatic stress disorder Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Panic attack Spanish verbs Methamphetamine Multiple sclerosis Autism Human height Kurt Cobain Robert Schumann Consensual crime Sigmund Freud Behavioral therapy Subjunctive mood Fibro